The extension of the mean model to multiply family types is straightforward (Appendix A.2 of the supplementary materials available at Biostatistics online). Equation (2.6) characterizes the approximate power of family-based studies for all combinations of affected and unaffected offspring with reference to small effect sizes (small relative risks). Our derivation thereby does not rely on an explicit analytic formula for the exact NCP. The latter is only known for some special cases as trios and sibling pairs (Deng and Chen, 2001; Knapp, 1999). Our results are in line with corresponding second order Taylor approximations of these NCPs in \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
